%I A395234 #39 Jun 01 2026 09:17:36
%S A395234 14,476075,364593585387
%N A395234 Number of cycles in K_{2n,2n,2n} minus a perfect matching.
%C A395234 Here cycles means simple cycles.
%C A395234 Regardless of which perfect matching is removed, the resulting graph is the same up to isomorphism.
%H A395234 Eric Weisstein's World of Mathematics, <a href="https://mathworld.wolfram.com/CompleteTripartiteGraphMinusPerfectMatching.html">Complete Tripartite Graph Minus Perfect Matching</a>.
%H A395234 Eric Weisstein's World of Mathematics, <a href="https://mathworld.wolfram.com/GraphCycle.html">Graph Cycle</a>.
%e A395234 a(1) = 14, since K_{2,2,2} minus a perfect matching is the 3-prism graph, which has 14 cycles.
%Y A395234 Cf. A393180 (perfect matchings in the same graph).
%Y A395234 Cf. A393586 (Hamiltonian cycles in the same graph).
%K A395234 nonn,more,bref
%O A395234 1,1
